<h2>Sonic Daybreak FAQ</h2>

<div class="details-grid">
<details>
<summary>Is Sonic Daybreak free?</summary>
<p>Yes. Sonic Daybreak is a non-profit fan game available as a free download. No accounts, no payments.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>What are the system requirements?</summary>
<p>Daybreak runs on Unreal Engine, so it needs a dedicated GPU. It works on lower-end PCs at minimum settings. Expect shader compilation stuttering on your first launch — performance improves after that.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Is this the full game?</summary>
<p>No. The current release is the SAGE 2025 demo with a tutorial and two full stages (Tropical Haven and Minty Slopes). The team has plans for additional levels and a complete story.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Should I use a controller or keyboard?</summary>
<p>Both work well. A gamepad is recommended for comfort, but the developers actually suggest keyboard + mouse for better camera control during platforming sections.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Why does the game stutter at the start?</summary>
<p>Unreal Engine compiles shaders on first launch. This causes temporary frame drops that disappear once all shaders are cached. Subsequent launches run smoothly.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Is there multiplayer?</summary>
<p>No. Sonic Daybreak is a single-player experience focused on platforming, exploration, and score-chasing through its ranking system.</p>
